verses.text_plain: And thou shalt make an altar to burn incense upon: of shittim wood shalt thou make it.
verses.verse_html: 1And thou shalt make an altar to burn incense upon: of shittim wood shalt thou make it.

verses.text_plain: A cubit shall be the length thereof, and a cubit the breadth thereof; foursquare shall it be: and two cubits shall be the height thereof: the horns thereof shall be of the same.
verses.verse_html: 2A cubit shall be the length thereof, and a cubit the breadth thereof; foursquare shall it be: and two cubits shall be the height thereof: the horns thereof shall be of the same.

tokens.text: shall it be: and two cubits

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt overlay it with pure gold, the top thereof, and the sides thereof round about, and the horns thereof; and thou shalt make unto it a crown of gold round about.
verses.verse_html:
3And thou shalt overlay it with pure gold, the top thereof, and the sides thereof round about, and the horns thereof; and thou shalt make unto it a crown of gold round about. ▼
▼ top: Heb. roof
 , ▼
▼ sides: Heb. walls

verses.text_plain: And two golden rings shalt thou make to it under the crown of it, by the two corners thereof, upon the two sides of it shalt thou make it; and they shall be for places for the staves to bear it withal.
verses.verse_html:
4And two golden rings shalt thou make to it under the crown of it, by the two corners thereof, upon the two sides of it shalt thou make it; and they shall be for places for the staves to bear it withal. ▼
▼ corners: Heb. ribs

tokens.text: and they shall be for places

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt make the staves of shittim wood, and overlay them with gold.
verses.verse_html: 5And thou shalt make the staves of shittim wood, and overlay them with gold.

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt put it before the vail that is by the ark of the testimony, before the mercy seat that is over the testimony, where I will meet with thee.
verses.verse_html: 6And thou shalt put it before the vail that is by the ark of the testimony, before the mercy seat that is over the testimony, where I will meet with thee.

verses.text_plain: And Aaron shall burn thereon sweet incense every morning: when he dresseth the lamps, he shall burn incense upon it.
verses.verse_html:
7And Aaron shall burn thereon sweet incense every morning: when he dresseth the lamps, he shall burn incense upon it. ▼

verses.text_plain: Ye shall offer no strange incense thereon, nor burnt sacrifice, nor meat offering; neither shall ye pour drink offering thereon.
verses.verse_html: 9Ye shall offer no strange incense thereon, nor burnt sacrifice, nor meat offering; neither shall ye pour drink offering thereon.

verses.text_plain: And Aaron shall make an atonement upon the horns of it once in a year with the blood of the sin offering of atonements: once in the year shall he make atonement upon it throughout your generations: it is most holy unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 10And Aaron shall make an atonement upon the horns of it once in a year with the blood of the sin offering of atonements: once in the year shall he make atonement upon it throughout your generations: it is most holy unto the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 11And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: When thou takest the sum of the children of Israel after their number, then shall they give every man a ransom for his soul unto the Lord, when thou numberest them; that there be no plague among them, when thou numberest them.
verses.verse_html:
12When thou takest the sum of the children of Israel after their number, then shall they give every man a ransom for his soul unto the Lord, when thou numberest them; that there be no plague among them, when thou numberest them. ▼
▼ their number: Heb. them that are to be numbered

tokens.text: them; that there be no plague

footnotes.body_text: ▼ their number: Heb. them that are to be numbered
footnotes.body_html: ▼ their number: Heb. them that are to be numbered

verses.text_plain: This they shall give, every one that passeth among them that are numbered, half a shekel after the shekel of the sanctuary: (a shekel is twenty gerahs:) an half shekel shall be the offering of the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 13This they shall give, every one that passeth among them that are numbered, half a shekel after the shekel of the sanctuary: (a shekel is twenty gerahs:) an half shekel shall be the offering of the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Every one that passeth among them that are numbered, from twenty years old and above, shall give an offering unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 14Every one that passeth among them that are numbered, from twenty years old and above, shall give an offering unto the Lord.

verses.text_plain: The rich shall not give more, and the poor shall not give less than half a shekel, when they give an offering unto the Lord, to make an atonement for your souls.
verses.verse_html:
15The rich shall not give more, and the poor shall not give less than half a shekel, when they give an offering unto the Lord, to make an atonement for your souls. ▼
▼ give more: Heb. multiply
 , ▼
▼ give less: Heb. diminish

footnotes.body_html: ▼ give more: Heb. multiply

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt take the atonement money of the children of Israel, and shalt appoint it for the service of the tabernacle of the congregation; that it may be a memorial unto the children of Israel before the Lord, to make an atonement for your souls.
verses.verse_html: 16And thou shalt take the atonement money of the children of Israel, and shalt appoint it for the service of the tabernacle of the congregation; that it may be a memorial unto the children of Israel before the Lord, to make an atonement for your souls.

tokens.text: that it may be a memorial

verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 17And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt also make a laver of brass, and his foot also of brass, to wash withal: and thou shalt put it between the tabernacle of the congregation and the altar, and thou shalt put water therein.
verses.verse_html: 18Thou shalt also make a laver of brass, and his foot also of brass, to wash withal: and thou shalt put it between the tabernacle of the congregation and the altar, and thou shalt put water therein.

verses.text_plain: For Aaron and his sons shall wash their hands and their feet thereat:
verses.verse_html: 19For Aaron and his sons shall wash their hands and their feet thereat:

verses.text_plain: When they go into the tabernacle of the congregation, they shall wash with water, that they die not; or when they come near to the altar to minister, to burn offering made by fire unto the Lord:
verses.verse_html: 20When they go into the tabernacle of the congregation, they shall wash with water, that they die not; or when they come near to the altar to minister, to burn offering made by fire unto the Lord:

verses.verse_html: 21So they shall wash their hands and their feet, that they die not: and it shall be a statute for ever to them, even to him and to his seed throughout their generations.

verses.text_plain: Moreover the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 22Moreover the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: Take thou also unto thee principal spices, of pure myrrh five hundred shekels, and of sweet cinnamon half so much, even two hundred and fifty shekels, and of sweet calamus two hundred and fifty shekels,
verses.verse_html: 23Take thou also unto thee principal spices, of pure myrrh five hundred shekels, and of sweet cinnamon half so much, even two hundred and fifty shekels, and of sweet calamus two hundred and fifty shekels,

verses.text_plain: And of cassia five hundred shekels, after the shekel of the sanctuary, and of oil olive an hin:
verses.verse_html: 24And of cassia five hundred shekels, after the shekel of the sanctuary, and of oil olive an hin:

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt make it an oil of holy ointment, an ointment compound after the art of the apothecary: it shall be an holy anointing oil.
verses.verse_html:
25And thou shalt make it an oil of holy ointment, an ointment compound after the art of the apothecary: it shall be an holy anointing oil. ▼

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt anoint the tabernacle of the congregation therewith, and the ark of the testimony,
verses.verse_html: 26And thou shalt anoint the tabernacle of the congregation therewith, and the ark of the testimony,

verses.text_plain: And the table and all his vessels, and the candlestick and his vessels, and the altar of incense,
verses.verse_html: 27And the table and all his vessels, and the candlestick and his vessels, and the altar of incense,

verses.text_plain: And the altar of burnt offering with all his vessels, and the laver and his foot.
verses.verse_html: 28And the altar of burnt offering with all his vessels, and the laver and his foot.

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt sanctify them, that they may be most holy: whatsoever toucheth them shall be holy.
verses.verse_html: 29And thou shalt sanctify them, that they may be most holy: whatsoever toucheth them shall be holy.

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt anoint Aaron and his sons, and consecrate them, that they may minister unto me in the priest’s office.
verses.verse_html: 30And thou shalt anoint Aaron and his sons, and consecrate them, that they may minister unto me in the priest’s office.

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt speak unto the children of Israel, saying, This shall be an holy anointing oil unto me throughout your generations.
verses.verse_html: 31And thou shalt speak unto the children of Israel, saying, This shall be an holy anointing oil unto me throughout your generations.

verses.text_plain: Upon man’s flesh shall it not be poured, neither shall ye make any other like it, after the composition of it: it is holy, and it shall be holy unto you.
verses.verse_html: 32Upon man’s flesh shall it not be poured, neither shall ye make any other like it, after the composition of it: it is holy, and it shall be holy unto you.

verses.verse_html: 33Whosoever compoundeth any like it, or whosoever putteth any of it upon a stranger, shall even be cut off from his people.
